### 🔹 1. Obtener todos los usuarios
GET http://localhost:3000/api/user
Accept: application/json

###

### 🔹 2. Registrar un usuario válido
POST http://localhost:3000/api/user/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "TEST@MAIL.COM",
  "password": "12345678",
  "name": "Test",
  "lastName": "Usuario",
  "nif": "12345678A"
}

###

### 🔹 3. Registrar un usuario con email duplicado (error 409)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/user/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "TEST@MAIL.COM",
  "password": "12345678",
  "name": "Test",
  "lastName": "Usuario",
  "nif": "12345678A",
  "status": "verified"
}

###

### 🔹 4. Registrar un usuario con email inválido (error 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/user/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "no-es-email",
  "password": "12345678",
  "name": "Test",
  "lastName": "Usuario",
  "nif": "12345678A"
}

###

### 🔹 5. Registrar un usuario con password corta (error 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/user/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "otrousuario@test.com",
  "password": "123",
  "name": "Test",
  "lastName": "Usuario",
  "nif": "12345678A"
}